What role does Group Policy play in Windows Active Directory?

    Group policy is a feature that allows administrators to manage and control the configuration settings for users and computers within a Windows domain, so its plays a huge role in Active Directory.

Name and describe different ways GPOs can benefit security.

    GPOs can benefit security by enforce password policy, configure account lockout settings, specify which users or groups have particular rights.

How can the acronym “LSDOU” help you figure out which policies are in effect?

    LSDOU can help figuring out which policies are in effect by understanding the order of the precedence in GPO´s.
